{"abstract": "We present Clifford-Steerable Convolutional Neural Networks (CS-CNNs), a novel class of $\\mathrm{E}(p, q)$-equivariant CNNs. CS-CNNs process multivector fields on pseudo-Euclidean spaces $\\mathbb{R}^{p,q}$. They cover, for instance, $\\mathrm{E}(3)$-equivariance on $\\mathbb{R}^3$ and Poincar\\'e-equivariance on Minkowski spacetime $\\mathbb{R}^{1,3}$. Our approach is based on an implicit parametrization of $\\mathrm{O}(p,q)$-steerable kernels via Clifford group equivariant neural networks. We significantly and consistently outperform baseline methods on fluid dynamics as well as relativistic electrodynamics forecasting tasks.", "referenced_work_ids": ["73a49b2efa1ca7815b67603f2831139c9cf0a2d7", "81e1ab8f0bc160286d156c7cd8efc87ad15f6f57", "4429bef4af76b9698ea951b84775e4a395f83ed8", "f72eb1835cdf29867ab78d66653b8dcde37bb7cb", "4689f6603587e64e87ae36a385e9aab34af2966a", "56c679a0d5fce962e1c09db6d762e4024e277450", "5f6c801ad83eb5266e08c67aaa1dda28597500a5", "ae9d5ae9f7ab573499f9864d9dec267e46a1d1a3", "c90de58527566c46cd2abd7cedfbf7f33334f43d", "00ffcc997b0bcf0dbf60ff04c29d701919582a62", "84959e211a767f902cbf1695ec54a5b50148020f", "2f54530751532106aeb689346f38720e63447ea6", "036aef17a8c2c03202170aa85fd7be1dba974202", "03170f9a8febe243bdfe23bc59000e6cf9c6fb24", "5852ca4ed260ef9049feb20fc86848e88628478d", "e9155ac8786f12c26cd7653804cec17fd1475359", "8d1118549b20c451abd0f412eb48a925922d98f8", "0d943f17e09cdb681f84c6bf3e7ea8b491bfdccc", "c12c87607371d095cb3e149fe20fef5acd9d116f", "1d5c8c6e5a774d2fef8d92bd28670a6345a97f7a", "7379045f1abe69ec6f89c53293ab1bb41fa156ec", "2f7dc1ee85e9f6a97810c66016e09ffeed684f03", "b6dc674b52da3c23a46843268d75a40e8b60be68", "c0b6a981cfa4847abb9e0aa23b67de3d85d7f4be", "5c6520df0bcc34c5fa83c66ff10770c25ab641b1", "456da28a3b6071a625857e8ccc16731f715055fb", "a9326f6eeaf16a171423b8a6627dd86d80af6ca6", "b626e35f2d30ac54a77e6d80b6fa8d01fa68971f", "563ca4cda06665f4b90f8fce9bcb28c02e6872b9", "412d0b5aa97e0713259d203e76f8a57b0357e0c9", "6a